-- Polish Stocks: Bank Pekao, Hydrobudowa, PBG, CEDC Move in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-04-23T16:20:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/polish-stocks-bank-pekao-hydrobudowa-pbg-cedc-move-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  slid 2.5
percent to a three-month low of 2,167.13 in Warsaw, the steepest
daily decline since Nov. 21.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Bank Pekao SA (PEO)  , the country’s second-largest
lender, fell 3.5 percent to a three-month low of 139 zloty after
Deutsche Bank AG cut its rating for the stock to hold from buy.  Hydrobudowa Polska (HBP)  SA, the Polish engineering
company controlled by  PBG SA (PBG)  , tumbled 20 percent to a
record low of 0.53 zloty after a creditor filed a motion to
declare the company bankrupt. PBG, the country’s third-biggest
builder, declined 21 percent to 22.5 zloty, also hitting an all-
time low.  Central European Distribution Corp. (CDC)  , Poland’s
second-biggest vodka producer, jumped the most in almost three
months after Russian Standard Corp. agreed to invest in its debt
and equity. The stock surged as much as 21 percent before
closing at 15.50, the highest since April 3 and up 13 percent on
the day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
